Overview: VMStat will report virtual memory statistics at regular intervals
using the VMStatReader operator.

The VMStatReader operator is a primitive opertor that looks into the
/proc/vmstat file to retreive periodic readings of memory statistics.

1. To build the sample application:
   make

2. To run the sample application:
   ./output/bin/standalone period=0.1 

Notes: 
  - The command line parameter 'period' is used to speciy the period in
    seconds (e.g. 0.1 seconds).

